detailedDescription.articleBody: Arizona is a state in the southwestern region of the United States. It is also part of the Western and the Mountain states. It is the 6th largest and the 14th most populous of the 50 states. Its capital and largest city is Phoenix.
detailedDescription.articleBodyHi: एरिज़ोना संयुक्त राज्य अमेरिका के दक्षिण-पश्चिमी क्षेत्र में एक राज्य है, यह पश्चिमी और पर्वतीय राज्यों का भी हिस्सा है, यह ५० राज्यों में ६ वां सबसे बड़ा और १४ वां सबसे अधिक आबादी वाला राज्य है, इसकी राजधानी और सबसे बड़ा शहर फीनिक्स है,

detailedDescription.articleBody: The Arizona Diamondbacks, often shortened as the D-backs, are an American professional baseball team based in Phoenix, Arizona. The Diamondbacks compete in Major League Baseball as a member club of the National League West division. The team plays its home games at Chase Field, formerly known as Bank One Ballpark.
detailedDescription.articleBodyHi: एरिज़ोना डायमंडबैक, जिसे अक्सर डी-बैक के रूप में छोटा किया जाता है, फीनिक्स, एरिज़ोना में स्थित एक अमेरिकी पेशेवर बेसबॉल टीम है, द डायमंडबैक नेशनल लीग वेस्ट डिवीजन के सदस्य क्लब के रूप में मेजर लीग बेसबॉल में प्रतिस्पर्धा करते हैं, टीम चेस में अपना घरेलू खेल खेलती है

detailedDescription.articleBody: The Arizona Coyotes are a professional ice hockey team based in the Phoenix metropolitan area. The Coyotes currently compete in the National Hockey League as a member of the Pacific Division in the Western Conference.

detailedDescription.articleBody: Isabella "Bella" Marie Cullen is a character and the protagonist of the Twilight novel series, written by Stephenie Meyer. The Twilight series, consisting of the novels Twilight, New Moon, Eclipse, and Breaking Dawn, is primarily narrated from Bella's point of view, but partway through Breaking Dawn it is written from Jacob Black's perspective.

Arizona State University is a public research university on five campuses across the Phoenix metropolitan area, and four regional learning centers throughout Arizona.
ASU is one of the largest public universities by enrollment in the U.S.
